==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: amygdalate
<hw>a*myg"da*late</hw> <pr>(⟦adot⟧*m⟦icr⟧g"d⟦adot⟧*l⟦asl⟧t)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>amygdala</ets>, <ets>amygdalum</ets>,
almond, Gr. <grk>'amygda`lh</grk>, <grk>'amy`gdalon</grk>. See
<er>Almond</er>.]</ety> <def>Pertaining to, resembling, or made of,
almonds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amygdalate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Amygdalate
<hw>A*myg"da*late</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>An emulsion made of almonds; milk of almonds.</def> <rj><au>Bailey.
Coxe.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>A salt of amygdalic acid. Called
also <altname>mandelate</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>amygdalic</ent>⟦br⟧
